social_posts.post_text: The honor of a lifetime to represent my country at the World Cup. Not the end we wanted but so proud of this incredible group. Left it all on the field. Thankful for all the support 🇺🇸

I couldn’t be happier with how my Dexcom G6 and Omnipod 5 have helped to keep my numbers in range. Before, I would be woken up almost every night with my numbers being too high or too low. But with the Omnipod 5, the automatic insulin adjustment has made my numbers throughout the night much more stable. This has allowed for better sleep and improved recovery, helping me to be at my best on the field 💪🏻 #Sponsored #DexcomWarrior @dexcom @omnipod
Raising the 12 flag was an unforgettable experience. Thanks so much @seahawks for having us!

Diabetes is a 24/7 job. It doesn’t stop for life’s big moments. Whether that is getting ready for a training or a game or spending a quiet day at home with my family, diabetes can be frustrating with unexpected highs or lows. For me, the most difficult part is managing that unpredictability. But when I talk to other kids living with diabetes, I always tell them that we were given diabetes because we are strong enough to handle it and push through these tough moments! I’m incredibly grateful for my support system and the amazing technology they helps make diabetes management easier like my Dexcom CGM and Omnipod 5. 
 
#Sponsored #DexcomWarrior @dexcom @omnipod

May is mental health awareness month and living with diabetes can really affect your mental health. The stress and burnout of living with diabetes daily is real and can feel isolating at times. For me, when I am struggling, I lean on my community of support. Being open and honest is incredibly helpful. I’m so grateful for my family, friends, and the diabetes community for supporting me and helping me get to where I am today. I am lucky enough to get to meet with lots of T1ds and those interactions with someone going through the same thing as you are so important. You empathize with the challenges that they are facing, but also gain so much inspiration from their triumphs. Knowing that I am not alone in this helps me get through tough times 💪🏻
